Description: Electric Guitar,Fender Stratocaster 40th Anniversary made in Mexico, Modified, Nice Neck. Don Lace pickups. Double Humbucker in bridge position.Good condition. Color is a bit yellowed. Some frets the varnish is worn a bit. Modified, I bought the guitar new in around 1999 from The Guitar Shoppe in Laguna Beach, CA.At some point I had one of the tone knobs removed because my hand would hit the Volume knob. Moved the volume knob down. I think I had the tones consolidated on the remaining tone knob. Notice the chrome plug where the volume knob was.No buzz just what ever is normal. The guitar weighs 7 lbs 14 oz. Has some blemishes. Not cleaned or polished. Great Guitar. Nice neck. Please inspect photo's and feel free to ask any questions.
